name: EID1
description_var_evidence: JAK2 V617F is not associated with lymphoid leukemia (B-lineage ALL, T-ALL or CLL).
source_name: The JAK2V617F activating mutation occurs in chronic myelomonocytic leukemia and acute myeloid leukemia, but not in acute lymphoblastic leukemia or chronic lymphocytic leukemia.

name: EID2
description_var_evidence: GIST tumors harboring PDGFRA D842V mutation are more likely to be benign than malignant.
source_name: A great majority of GISTs with PDGFRA mutations represent gastric tumors of low or no malignant potential.
source_full_journal_title: Laboratory investigation; a journal of technical methods and pathology

name: EID3
description_var_evidence: DNMT3A R882 mutations occur most often in de novo AML patients with intermediate risk cytogenetics (39/194 intermediate risk patients vs 0/89 low and high risk).
source_name: Do AML patients with DNMT3A exon 23 mutations benefit from idarubicin as compared to daunorubicin? A single center experience.

name: EID4
description_var_evidence: Young AML patients (<60 years old) with DNMT3A mutations (60% of which were R882) were older in age, had higher white blood cell counts and had higher platelet counts than patients wildtype for DNMT3A.
source_name: Mutant DNMT3A: a marker of poor prognosis in acute myeloid leukemia.

name: EID5
description_var_evidence: JAK2 V617F is associated with myeloid malignanices (AML, MDS, CMML/atypical CML).
source_name: The JAK2V617F activating mutation occurs in chronic myelomonocytic leukemia and acute myeloid leukemia, but not in acute lymphoblastic leukemia or chronic lymphocytic leukemia.

name: EID6
description_var_evidence: JAK2 V617F is associated with myeloid neoplasms (AML, MDS, CMML/aCML).
source_name: The JAK2V617F activating mutation occurs in chronic myelomonocytic leukemia and acute myeloid leukemia, but not in acute lymphoblastic leukemia or chronic lymphocytic leukemia.

name: EID7
description_var_evidence: The SNP rs10974944 in the Jak2 locus is associated with increased predisposition for JAK2 V617F mutation and its associated cancer.
source_name: A germline JAK2 SNP is associated with predisposition to the development of JAK2(V617F)-positive myeloproliferative neoplasms.

name: EID8
description_var_evidence: Children with early age leukaemia who had second hand smoke exposure are more likely to harbor KRAS mutation.
source_name: RAS mutations in early age leukaemia modulated by NQO1 rs1800566 (C609T) are associated with second-hand smoking exposures.

name: EID10
description_var_evidence: Melanoma associated with NRAS Q61 mutation was more often associated with those at the extremity than those at the trunk.
source_name: NRAS and BRAF mutations in melanoma-associated nevi and uninvolved nevi.

name: EID11
description_var_evidence: Daunorubicin treatment resulted in similar overall survival and disease free survival in de novo AML patients with DNMT3A R882 mutation compared to those who do not harbor this mutation.
source_name: Do AML patients with DNMT3A exon 23 mutations benefit from idarubicin as compared to daunorubicin? A single center experience.

name: EID12
description_var_evidence: A375 cells expressing MAP2K1 P124S mutation conferred an approximately 5-fold increased resistance to selumetinib (AZD6244) induced growth inhibition when compared to untransduced cells, cells expressing wild-type MAP2K1 or cells expressing a constitutively active form. This mutation also attenuated pERK inhibition by selumetinib in these cells.
source_name: MEK1 mutations confer resistance to MEK and B-RAF inhibition.
source_citation: Emery et al., 2009, Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U.S.A.
source_full_journal_title: Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America

name: EID13
description_var_evidence: A375 cells expressing MAP2K1 Q56P mutation conferred an approximately 100-fold increased resistance to selumetinib (AZD6244) induced growth inhibition when compared to untransduced cells, cells expressing wild-type MAP2K1, or cells expressing a constitutively active form. This mutation also attenuated pERK inhibition by selumetinib in these cells.
source_name: MEK1 mutations confer resistance to MEK and B-RAF inhibition.
source_citation: Emery et al., 2009, Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U.S.A.
source_full_journal_title: Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America

name: EID14
description_var_evidence: Vemurafenib resistance is associated with gain of Q61 mutation in NRAS.
source_name: Pharmacodynamic effects and mechanisms of resistance to vemurafenib in patients with metastatic melanoma.
source_citation: Trunzer et al., 2013, J. Clin. Oncol.
source_full_journal_title: Journal of clinical oncology : official journal of the American Society of Clinical Oncology

name: EID15
description_var_evidence: GIST cancer with D842V mutation is resistant to imatinib.
source_name: PDGFRA mutations in gastrointestinal stromal tumors: frequency, spectrum and in vitro sensitivity to imatinib.
source_citation: Corless et al., 2005, J. Clin. Oncol.
source_full_journal_title: Journal of clinical oncology : official journal of the American Society of Clinical Oncology

name: EID16
description_var_evidence: While cancer with PDGFRA V561D mutation is known to be sensitive to Imatinib, double mutation of V561D and D842V mutants are resistant to imatinib.
source_name: Molecular correlates of imatinib resistance in gastrointestinal stromal tumors.
source_citation: Heinrich et al., 2006, J. Clin. Oncol.
source_full_journal_title: Journal of clinical oncology : official journal of the American Society of Clinical Oncology

name: EID17
description_var_evidence: In one patient with S214C mutation, the use of sorafenib has led to more than 5 years of survival and near remission.
source_name: Oncogenic and sorafenib-sensitive ARAF mutations in lung adenocarcinoma.
source_citation: Imielinski et al., 2014, J. Clin. Invest.

name: EID18
description_var_evidence: Idarubicin increases the overall survival and disease free survival in de novo AML patients with DNMT3A R882 mutation compared to those who do not harbor this mutation.
source_name: Do AML patients with DNMT3A exon 23 mutations benefit from idarubicin as compared to daunorubicin? A single center experience.

name: EID19
description_var_evidence: In patients with JAK2 V617F, the use of pegylated IFN-alpha-2a leads to reduction in the percentage of cells harboring JAK2 V617F.
source_name: High molecular response rate of polycythemia vera patients treated with pegylated interferon alpha-2a.

name: EID20
description_var_evidence: TG101348 effectively inhibits STAT5 signaling in JAK2 V617F cells.
source_name: Efficacy of TG101348, a selective JAK2 inhibitor, in treatment of a murine model of JAK2V617F-induced polycythemia vera.

name: EID21
description_var_evidence: Likely due to increased reliance of mutant NRAS on HSP90 for stabilization, inhibition of HSP90 by 17-AAG was shown to be effective in a patient with metastatic malignant melanoma with an NRAS G13D mutation.
source_name: BRAF and NRAS mutations in melanoma: potential relationships to clinical response to HSP90 inhibitors.
source_citation: Banerji et al., 2008, Mol. Cancer Ther.

name: EID22
description_var_evidence: In a melanoma patient with NRAS Q61L mutation, treatment with temozolomide resulted in disease free survival of 14 months.
source_name: NRAS-mutant melanoma: response to chemotherapy.

name: EID23
description_var_evidence: In a melanoma patient with Q61R mutation, treatment with temozolomide resulted in overall survival of 16 months.
source_name: NRAS-mutant melanoma: response to chemotherapy.

name: EID24
description_var_evidence: There is no difference in the complete remission rate of de novo AML patients with DNMT3A mutation compared to those who are wild type for DNMT3A.
source_name: Do AML patients with DNMT3A exon 23 mutations benefit from idarubicin as compared to daunorubicin? A single center experience.

name: EID25
description_var_evidence: De novo AML patients with DNMT3A D882 mutation showed worse survival (event-free and overall) outcome than those without DNMT3A mutation.
source_name: DNMT3A mutations in acute myeloid leukemia.
source_citation: Ley et al., 2010, N. Engl. J. Med.
source_full_journal_title: The New England journal of medicine

name: EID26
description_var_evidence: In acute myloid leukemia patients, D816 mutation is associated with earlier relapse and poorer prognosis than wildtype KIT.
source_name: Prognostic impact of c-KIT mutations in core binding factor leukemias: an Italian retrospective study.

name: EID27
description_var_evidence: Patients with colorectal cancer harboring NRAS mutation have poorer survival outcome and worse prognosis than patients with wildtype NRAS.
source_name: The predictive value of KRAS, NRAS, BRAF, PIK3CA and PTEN for anti-EGFR treatment in metastatic colorectal cancer: A systematic review and meta-analysis.

name: EID30
description_var_evidence: BRAF mutations are associated with melanoma arising in non-chronic sun damaged skin and with superficial spreading melanoma.
source_name: Frequencies of BRAF and NRAS mutations are different in histological types and sites of origin of cutaneous melanoma: a meta-analysis.
source_citation: Lee et al., 2011, Br. J. Dermatol.

name: EID31
description_var_evidence: DNMT3A R882 mutations were associated with older age, higher white blood cell count, and FAB M4 and M5 subtypes compared to wildtype DNMT3A in a cohort of cytogenetically normal AML patients.
source_name: DNMT3A R882 mutations in patients with cytogenetically normal acute myeloid leukemia and myelodysplastic syndrome.
source_citation: El Ghannam et al., Blood Cells Mol. Dis.

name: EID32
description_var_evidence: Ba/F3 cells expressing the RANBP2-ALK fusion containing an F1174L mutation were more resistant to crizotinib treatment than Ba/F3 cells expressing RANBP2-ALK without this mutation.
source_name: The neuroblastoma-associated F1174L ALK mutation causes resistance to an ALK kinase inhibitor in ALK-translocated cancers.

name: EID33
description_var_evidence: Ba/F3 cells expressing the EML4-ALK fusion containing an F1174L mutation were more resistant to crizotinib treatment than Ba/F3 cells expressing EML4-ALK without this mutation.
source_name: The neuroblastoma-associated F1174L ALK mutation causes resistance to an ALK kinase inhibitor in ALK-translocated cancers.

name: EID34
description_var_evidence: The melanoma cell line WM3211, which harbors the L576P mutation, is not sensitive to imatinib, nilotinib, and sorafenib. Molecular modeling indicated the L576P mutation alters the conformation of KIT and reduces the binding affinity of imatinib.
source_name: Activity of dasatinib against L576P KIT mutant melanoma: molecular, cellular, and clinical correlates.
source_citation: Woodman et al., 2009, Mol. Cancer Ther.

name: EID35
description_var_evidence: In NSCLC, Exon 2 KRAS mutations were associated with resistance to the EGFR kinase inhibitors gefitinib and erlotinib.
source_name: KRAS mutations and primary resistance of lung adenocarcinomas to gefitinib or erlotinib.

name: EID36
description_var_evidence: Chemotherapy-refractory patients with colorectal cancer harboring NRAS mutation (primarily Q61) have a significantly lower response rate to cetuximab than patients wildtype for NRAS.
source_name: Effects of KRAS, BRAF, NRAS, and PIK3CA mutations on the efficacy of cetuximab plus chemotherapy in chemotherapy-refractory metastatic colorectal cancer: a retrospective consortium analysis.
source_citation: De Roock et al., 2010, Lancet Oncol.

name: EID37
description_var_evidence: CH5424802 is effective in inhibiting the activity of the F1174L ALK mutant in a kinase activity assay and proliferation assay using neuroblastoma KELLY cells.
source_name: CH5424802, a selective ALK inhibitor capable of blocking the resistant gatekeeper mutant.

name: EID38
description_var_evidence: High levels of crizotinib can overcome drug resistance of Ba/F3 cells expressing the EML4-ALK fusion containing the F1174L mutation.
source_name: ALK mutations conferring differential resistance to structurally diverse ALK inhibitors.
source_citation: Heuckmann et al., 2011, Clin. Cancer Res.
source_full_journal_title: Clinical cancer research : an official journal of the American Association for Cancer Research

name: EID39
description_var_evidence: TAE684 inhibits growth of Ba/F3 cells expressing ALK mutations; however, cells with the R1275Q mutation were inhibited at a higher IC50 than those expressing F1174L.
source_name: Activating mutations in ALK provide a therapeutic target in neuroblastoma.

name: EID40
description_var_evidence: Sorafenib can inhibit ARF-mediated MEK phosphorylation and soft agar colony formation of AALE cells expressing ARAF S214C in vitro.
source_name: Oncogenic and sorafenib-sensitive ARAF mutations in lung adenocarcinoma.
source_citation: Imielinski et al., 2014, J. Clin. Invest.

name: EID41
description_var_evidence: Trametinib can inhibit ARF-mediated ERK phosphorylation and soft agar colony formation of AALE cells expressing ARAF S214C in vitro.
source_name: Oncogenic and sorafenib-sensitive ARAF mutations in lung adenocarcinoma.
source_citation: Imielinski et al., 2014, J. Clin. Invest.

name: EID42
description_var_evidence: The melanoma cell line WM3211, which harbors the L576P mutation, is sensitive to dasatinib. Molecular modeling indicated the L576P mutation alters the conformation of KIT but did not alter the binding affinity of dasatinib.
source_name: Activity of dasatinib against L576P KIT mutant melanoma: molecular, cellular, and clinical correlates.
source_citation: Woodman et al., 2009, Mol. Cancer Ther.

name: EID43
description_var_evidence: In CHO cells with PDGFRA D842I mutation that have shown imatinib resistance, crenolanib was significantly more potent at inhibiting kinase activity than imatinib.
source_name: Crenolanib inhibits the drug-resistant PDGFRA D842V mutation associated with imatinib-resistant gastrointestinal stromal tumors.
source_citation: Heinrich et al., 2012, Clin. Cancer Res.
source_full_journal_title: Clinical cancer research : an official journal of the American Association for Cancer Research

name: EID44
description_var_evidence: In CHO cells with PDGFRA D842V mutation that have shown imatinib resistance, crenolanib was significantly more potent at inhibiting kinase activity than imatinib.
source_name: Crenolanib inhibits the drug-resistant PDGFRA D842V mutation associated with imatinib-resistant gastrointestinal stromal tumors.
source_citation: Heinrich et al., 2012, Clin. Cancer Res.
source_full_journal_title: Clinical cancer research : an official journal of the American Association for Cancer Research

name: EID45
description_var_evidence: In CHO cells with PDGFRA D842Y mutation that have shown imatinib resistance, crenolanib was significantly more potent at inhibiting kinase activity than imatinib.
source_name: Crenolanib inhibits the drug-resistant PDGFRA D842V mutation associated with imatinib-resistant gastrointestinal stromal tumors.
source_citation: Heinrich et al., 2012, Clin. Cancer Res.
source_full_journal_title: Clinical cancer research : an official journal of the American Association for Cancer Research

name: EID46
description_var_evidence: In CHO cells with the PDGFRA deletion I843 mutation that have shown imatinib sensitivity, crenolanib showed no significant difference from imatinib in kinase activity inhibition.
source_name: Crenolanib inhibits the drug-resistant PDGFRA D842V mutation associated with imatinib-resistant gastrointestinal stromal tumors.
source_citation: Heinrich et al., 2012, Clin. Cancer Res.
source_full_journal_title: Clinical cancer research : an official journal of the American Association for Cancer Research

name: EID47
description_var_evidence: In CHO cells with PDGFRA DI842-843VM mutation that have shown imatinib resistance, crenolanib was significantly more potent at inhibiting kinase activity than imatinib.
source_name: Crenolanib inhibits the drug-resistant PDGFRA D842V mutation associated with imatinib-resistant gastrointestinal stromal tumors.
source_citation: Heinrich et al., 2012, Clin. Cancer Res.
source_full_journal_title: Clinical cancer research : an official journal of the American Association for Cancer Research

name: EID48
description_var_evidence: The SMS-KCNR cell line harboring the R1275Q mutation was resistant to TAE684.
source_name: Activating mutations in ALK provide a therapeutic target in neuroblastoma.

name: EID49
description_var_evidence: In a large cohort of AML patients (mean = 48 years), DNMT3A mutation (64.5% of which were R882) had no prognostic value on overall, relapse free and event free survival.
source_name: Clinical impact of DNMT3A mutations in younger adult patients with acute myeloid leukemia: results of the AML Study Group (AMLSG).

name: EID50
description_var_evidence: In a large cohort (n=1770) of AML patients (18-60 years old), DNMT3A mutation status (65.4% of which were R882) had no prognostic value for overall, relapse free and event free survival. This was true for cytogenetically normal AML and the entire cohort.
source_name: Clinical impact of DNMT3A mutations in younger adult patients with acute myeloid leukemia: results of the AML Study Group (AMLSG).

name: EID51
description_var_evidence: In young AML patients (<60 years old), DNMT3A mutation status (60% of which were R882) was not predictive of overall and relapse free survival in patients with NPM1 mutations and wildtype FLT3 or wildtype NPM1 and FLT3-ITD.
source_name: Mutant DNMT3A: a marker of poor prognosis in acute myeloid leukemia.

name: EID52
description_var_evidence: In young AML patients (<60 years old), DNMT3A mutation status was not predictive of overall and relapse free survival in patients with NPM1 mutations and wildtype FLT3 or wildtype NPM1 and FLT3-ITD.
source_name: Mutant DNMT3A: a marker of poor prognosis in acute myeloid leukemia.

name: EID53
description_var_evidence: There is no significant association between wildtype KIT or KIT mutations in exon 9 or 11 in survival among GIST patients.
source_name: Polyclonal evolution of multiple secondary KIT mutations in gastrointestinal stromal tumors under treatment with imatinib mesylate.
source_citation: Wardelmann et al., 2006, Clin. Cancer Res.
source_full_journal_title: Clinical cancer research : an official journal of the American Association for Cancer Research

name: EID56
description_var_evidence: The presence of NRAS mutation in AML patients does not impact diease prognosis (resistant disease, disease-free survival, complete remission rate, relapse rate, induction death).
source_name: RAS mutation in acute myeloid leukemia is associated with distinct cytogenetic subgroups but does not influence outcome in patients younger than 60 years.

name: EID57
description_var_evidence: NRAS mutation status does not impact overall, event-free or disease-free survival in patients with AML.
source_name: Implications of NRAS mutations in AML: a study of 2502 patients.

name: EID58
description_var_evidence: Melanoma patients with KIT mutation but not KIT amplification showed response to imatinib treatment in a small cohort of patients.
source_name: Imatinib for melanomas harboring mutationally activated or amplified KIT arising on mucosal, acral, and chronically sun-damaged skin.
source_citation: Hodi et al., 2013, J. Clin. Oncol.
source_full_journal_title: Journal of clinical oncology : official journal of the American Society of Clinical Oncology

name: EID61
description_var_evidence: In a large cohort of young AML patients (18-60 years old), DNMT3A R882 mutations were associated with reduced relapse free survival in the entire cohort as well as the subset of patients with cytogenetically normal AML.
source_name: Clinical impact of DNMT3A mutations in younger adult patients with acute myeloid leukemia: results of the AML Study Group (AMLSG).

name: EID62
description_var_evidence: AML patients with DNMT3A mutations (59% of which were R882) showed worse survival (event-free and overall) outcome than those without DNMT3A mutation.
source_name: DNMT3A mutations in acute myeloid leukemia.
source_citation: Ley et al., 2010, N. Engl. J. Med.
source_full_journal_title: The New England journal of medicine

name: EID63
description_var_evidence: DNMT3A R882 mutation was associated with reduced relapse free and overall survival in ELN-unfavorable, cytogenetically normal AMLs.
source_name: Clinical impact of DNMT3A mutations in younger adult patients with acute myeloid leukemia: results of the AML Study Group (AMLSG).

name: EID64
description_var_evidence: In AML patients with FLT3-ITD mutations, concurrent DNMT3A mutations (including R882) were associated with worse overall survival compared to those without DNMT3A mutation.
source_name: DNMT3A mutations in acute myeloid leukemia.
source_citation: Ley et al., 2010, N. Engl. J. Med.
source_full_journal_title: The New England journal of medicine

name: EID65
description_var_evidence: In cytogenetically normal AML patients, DNMT3A R882 mutations are associated with lower overall and disease free survival as compared to patients with wild type DNMT3A.
source_name: DNMT3A R882 mutations in patients with cytogenetically normal acute myeloid leukemia and myelodysplastic syndrome.
source_citation: El Ghannam et al., Blood Cells Mol. Dis.

name: EID66
description_var_evidence: In older cytogenetically normal AML patients (>59 years), DNMT3A R882 mutation is prognostic for shorter disease free survival and overall survival compared to patients without the mutation.
source_name: Age-related prognostic impact of different types of DNMT3A mutations in adults with primary cytogenetically normal acute myeloid leukemia.
source_citation: Marcucci et al., 2012, J. Clin. Oncol.
source_full_journal_title: Journal of clinical oncology : official journal of the American Society of Clinical Oncology

name: EID67
description_var_evidence: In young AML patients (<60 years old), DNMT3A mutations were associated with significantly reduced overall survival and relapse free survival in patients wildtype for NPM1 and FLT3.
source_name: Mutant DNMT3A: a marker of poor prognosis in acute myeloid leukemia.

name: EID68
description_var_evidence: In younger cytogenetically normal AML patients (<60 years), DNMT3A mutations other than R882 are prognostic for shorter disease free survival and overall survival compared to patients without the mutation.
source_name: Age-related prognostic impact of different types of DNMT3A mutations in adults with primary cytogenetically normal acute myeloid leukemia.
source_citation: Marcucci et al., 2012, J. Clin. Oncol.
source_full_journal_title: Journal of clinical oncology : official journal of the American Society of Clinical Oncology

name: EID69
description_var_evidence: In AML patients with FLT3-ITD mutations, concurrent DNMT3A mutations were associated with worse overall survival compared to those without DNMT3A mutation.
source_name: DNMT3A mutations in acute myeloid leukemia.
source_citation: Ley et al., 2010, N. Engl. J. Med.
source_full_journal_title: The New England journal of medicine

name: EID70
description_var_evidence: GIST patients with exon 14 KIT mutations had reduced overall survival compared to patients wiltype for KIT.
source_name: Polyclonal evolution of multiple secondary KIT mutations in gastrointestinal stromal tumors under treatment with imatinib mesylate.
source_citation: Wardelmann et al., 2006, Clin. Cancer Res.
source_full_journal_title: Clinical cancer research : an official journal of the American Association for Cancer Research

name: EID71
description_var_evidence: In patients with stage IV melanoma, NRAS mutation was associated with reduced median survival compared to patients with wildtype NRAS.
source_name: NRAS mutation status is an independent prognostic factor in metastatic melanoma.

name: EID73
description_var_evidence: A single patient with BRAF V600E/V600M bi-allelic mutation responded to the V600E drug dabrafenib.
source_name: Overwhelming response to Dabrafenib in a patient with double BRAF mutation (V600E; V600M) metastatic malignant melanoma.
source_citation: Ponti et al., 2012, J Hematol Oncol

name: EID74
description_var_evidence: In patients with medullary carcinoma, the presence of RET M918T mutation is associated with increased probability of lymph node metastases.
source_name: Prognostic significance of somatic RET oncogene mutations in sporadic medullary thyroid cancer: a 10-year follow-up study.
source_citation: Elisei et al., 2008, J. Clin. Endocrinol. Metab.
source_full_journal_title: The Journal of clinical endocrinology and metabolism

name: EID75
description_var_evidence: Medullary thyroid cancer cells with RET C634W mutation are insensitive to motesanib, compared to wild-type RET.
source_name: Anti-tumor activity of motesanib in a medullary thyroid cancer model.
source_citation: Coxon et al., 2012, J. Endocrinol. Invest.

name: EID76
description_var_evidence: Medullary thyroid cancer cells with RET M918T mutation are insensitive to motesanib, compared to wild-type RET.
source_name: Anti-tumor activity of motesanib in a medullary thyroid cancer model.
source_citation: Coxon et al., 2012, J. Endocrinol. Invest.

name: EID77
description_var_evidence: The use of AZD1480 on RET-mutated/rearranged cell lines in vitro led to strong repression of tyroid cancer cell growth.
source_name: AZD1480 blocks growth and tumorigenesis of RET- activated thyroid cancer cell lines.

name: EID78
description_var_evidence: Compared to those who harbor a wild type RET, patients with RET M918T mutation develop larger and more aggressive medullary thyroid cancer.
source_name: Genotype-phenotype correlation of patients with multiple endocrine neoplasia type 2 in Japan.
source_citation: Egawa et al., 1998, Jpn. J. Clin. Oncol.

name: EID79
description_var_evidence: BRAF V600E is shown to be associated with the tall-cell variant of papillary thyroid cancer.
source_name: Both BRAF V600E mutation and older age (â‰¥ 65 years) are associated with recurrent papillary thyroid cancer.
source_citation: Howell et al., 2011, Ann. Surg. Oncol.

name: EID80
description_var_evidence: Thyroid nodule with BRAF V600E mutation is highly correlated with papillary thyroid cancer.
source_name: Immunohistochemistry for BRAF(V600E) antibody VE1 performed in core needle biopsy samples identifies mutated papillary thyroid cancers.
source_citation: Crescenzi et al., 2014, Horm. Metab. Res.
source_full_journal_title: Hormone and metabolic research = Hormon- und Stoffwechselforschung = Hormones et meÌtabolisme

name: EID82
description_var_evidence: BRAF status does not predict prognosis in patients treated with dacarbazine or temozolomide.
source_name: BRAF-V600 mutations have no prognostic impact in stage IV melanoma patients treated with monochemotherapy.

name: EID83
description_var_evidence: PIK3CA mutation status was not predictive of response to regorafenib treatment in patients that had received standard therapy and progressed within 3 months of their last treatment.
source_name: Regorafenib in metastatic colorectal cancer.
source_citation: Sartore-Bianchi et al., 2014, Expert Rev Anticancer Ther

name: EID86
description_var_evidence: In the setting of BRAF(V600E), NF1 loss resulted in elevated activation of RAS-GTP but does not show resistance to MEK inhibitors.
source_name: Loss of NF1 in cutaneous melanoma is associated with RAS activation and MEK dependence.

name: EID87
description_var_evidence: KRAS mutation status was not predictive of response to regorafenib treatment in patients that had received standard therapy and progressed within 3 months of their last treatment.
source_name: Regorafenib in metastatic colorectal cancer.
source_citation: Sartore-Bianchi et al., 2014, Expert Rev Anticancer Ther

name: EID88
description_var_evidence: In metastatic colorectal cancer patients with wildtype KRAS, BRAF mutations were associated with poor progression free survival regardless of treatment (panitumumab with best supportive care or best supportive care alone).
source_name: Massively parallel tumor multigene sequencing to evaluate response to panitumumab in a randomized phase III study of metastatic colorectal cancer.
source_citation: Peeters et al., 2013, Clin. Cancer Res.
source_full_journal_title: Clinical cancer research : an official journal of the American Association for Cancer Research

name: EID89
description_var_evidence: Cetuximab or panitumumab may be ineffective in patients with BRAF mutation unless BRAF inhibitor such as Sorafenib is introduced.
source_name: Wild-type BRAF is required for response to panitumumab or cetuximab in metastatic colorectal cancer.
source_citation: Di Nicolantonio et al., 2008, J. Clin. Oncol.
source_full_journal_title: Journal of clinical oncology : official journal of the American Society of Clinical Oncology

name: EID90
description_var_evidence: In the setting of BRAF(V600E), NF1 loss resulted in elevated activation of RAS-GTP and resistance to RAF inhibitors.
source_name: Loss of NF1 in cutaneous melanoma is associated with RAS activation and MEK dependence.

name: EID91
description_var_evidence: In a patient with V600E-positive NSCLC, KRAS G12D seemed to confer resistance to dabrafenib.
source_name: Molecular characterization of acquired resistance to the BRAF inhibitor dabrafenib in a patient with BRAF-mutant non-small-cell lung cancer.
source_citation: Rudin et al., 2013, J Thorac Oncol
source_full_journal_title: Journal of thoracic oncology : official publication of the International Association for the Study of Lung Cancer

name: EID92
description_var_evidence: COLO201 and COLO206F cells harboring BRAF V600E mutations were cloned to be MEK inhibitor (AZD6244 [selumetinib]) resistant. The mechanism of this resistance was shown to be amplification of the BRAF V600E gene.
source_name: BRAF gene amplification can promote acquired resistance to MEK inhibitors in cancer cells harboring the BRAF V600E mutation.

name: EID93
description_var_evidence: Melanoma patients with BRAF V600E/K mutations had longer progression-free survival, increased tumor regression,  and increased duration of response to combined dabrafenib and trametinib treatment compared to dabrafenib alone.
source_name: Combined BRAF and MEK inhibition in melanoma with BRAF V600 mutations.
source_citation: Flaherty et al., 2012, N. Engl. J. Med.
source_full_journal_title: The New England journal of medicine

name: EID94
description_var_evidence: Patients with other BRAF V600 mutations also respond well to the V600E drug dabrafenib.
source_name: The somatic affairs of BRAF: tailored therapies for advanced malignant melanoma and orphan non-V600E (V600R-M) mutations.
source_citation: Ponti et al., 2013, J. Clin. Pathol.

name: EID95
description_var_evidence: Dabrafenib with trametinib provides higher response rate and lower toxicity (as compared to chemotherapy) in patients with melanoma.
source_name: Dabrafenib and trametinib, alone and in combination for BRAF-mutant metastatic melanoma.
source_citation: Menzies et al., 2014, Clin. Cancer Res.
source_full_journal_title: Clinical cancer research : an official journal of the American Association for Cancer Research

name: EID96
description_var_evidence: Combined MEK inhibitor PD0325901 and BRAF inhibitor PLX4720 administration to NSG mice subcutanousely injected with colorectal cell lines with a BRAF V600E mutation effectively inhibited tumor growth and reduced cellular proliferation.
source_name: A genetic progression model of Braf(V600E)-induced intestinal tumorigenesis reveals targets for therapeutic intervention.

name: EID97
description_var_evidence: Combined nutlin-3 and PLX4720 administration to athymic nude mice subcutanousely injected with the A357 colorectal cell line with a BRAF V600E mutation effectively inhibited tumor growth significantly more than single agent therapy.
source_name: Vemurafenib synergizes with nutlin-3 to deplete survivin and suppresses melanoma viability and tumor growth.
source_citation: Ji et al., 2013, Clin. Cancer Res.
source_full_journal_title: Clinical cancer research : an official journal of the American Association for Cancer Research

name: EID98
description_var_evidence: Mouse xenografts using HT29 cells harboring the BRAF V600E mutation treated with combination therapy (capecitabine, vemurafenib, bevacizumab) showed increased survival and reduced tumor burden compared to single and double agent therapies.
source_name: Antitumor activity of BRAF inhibitor vemurafenib in preclinical models of BRAF-mutant colorectal cancer.

name: EID99
description_var_evidence: Cell lines expressing the BRAF V600E mutation responded better to vemurafenib treatment than cells wildtype for BRAF as measured by reduced cellular proliferation and inhibition of MET and ERK phosphorylation.
source_name: Antitumor activity of BRAF inhibitor vemurafenib in preclinical models of BRAF-mutant colorectal cancer.

name: EID102
description_var_evidence: Unlike other studies that suggest a poorer outcome, BRAF mutation in this study was not correlated with poorer prognosis in papillary thyroid cancer.
source_name: The BRAF(V600E) mutation in papillary thyroid microcarcinoma: does the mutation have an impact on clinical outcome?

name: EID103
description_var_evidence: V600E is associated with adverse pathological features of colorectal cancer. This can be concluded as a marker of poor prognosis.
source_name: BRAFV600E mutation and its association with clinicopathological features of colorectal cancer: a systematic review and meta-analysis.

name: EID104
description_var_evidence: BRAF V600E is correlated with shorter disease-free and overall Survival in a Spanish cohort of melanoma patients.
source_name: Prognostic value of BRAF mutations in localized cutaneous melanoma.
source_citation: Nagore et al., 2014, J. Am. Acad. Dermatol.
source_full_journal_title: Journal of the American Academy of Dermatology

name: EID105
description_var_evidence: BRAF mutation correlated with poor prognosis in papillary thyroid cancer in both older (>65 yo) and younger (<65 yo) cohorts.
source_name: Both BRAF V600E mutation and older age (â‰¥ 65 years) are associated with recurrent papillary thyroid cancer.
source_citation: Howell et al., 2011, Ann. Surg. Oncol.

name: EID106
description_var_evidence: BRAF V600E is correlated with poor prognosis in papillary thyroid cancer in a study of 187 patients with PTC and other thyroid diseases.
source_name: Prognostic value of the BRAF V600E mutation in papillary thyroid carcinoma.

name: EID107
description_var_evidence: V600E is correlated with disease recurrence in both age cohorts (>65 and <65 yo).
source_name: Both BRAF V600E mutation and older age (â‰¥ 65 years) are associated with recurrent papillary thyroid cancer.
source_citation: Howell et al., 2011, Ann. Surg. Oncol.

name: EID108
description_var_evidence: NPM1 mutations were not associated with the M3 acute myeloid leukemia FAB subtype (0/55).
source_name: Prevalence and prognostic impact of NPM1 mutations in 1485 adult patients with acute myeloid leukemia (AML).

name: EID109
description_var_evidence: No NPM1 mutations were identified in patients with favorable risk cytogenetics (79/215 patients).
source_name: DNMT3A mutations in acute myeloid leukemia.
source_citation: Ley et al., 2010, N. Engl. J. Med.
source_full_journal_title: The New England journal of medicine

name: EID110
description_var_evidence: Therapy-related AML was less common in patients with DNMT3A mutations (64.5% of which were R882) than patients wildtype for DNMT3A in a large cohort of younger (18-60) AML patients.
source_name: Clinical impact of DNMT3A mutations in younger adult patients with acute myeloid leukemia: results of the AML Study Group (AMLSG).

name: EID111
description_var_evidence: NPM1 mutations were not associated with the M2 FAB subtype of acute myeloid leukemia.
source_name: Nucleophosmin gene mutations are predictors of favorable prognosis in acute myelogenous leukemia with a normal karyotype.

name: EID112
description_var_evidence: DNMT3A mutations (59% of which were R882) were associated with an intermediate risk cytogenetic profile, normal cytogenetic profile, and M4 and M5 FAB subtypes.
source_name: DNMT3A mutations in acute myeloid leukemia.
source_citation: Ley et al., 2010, N. Engl. J. Med.
source_full_journal_title: The New England journal of medicine

name: EID113
description_var_evidence: DNMT3A mutations (59% of which were R882) were associated with intermediate risk cytogenetics (including normal karyotype).
source_name: DNMT3A mutations in acute myeloid leukemia.
source_citation: Ley et al., 2010, N. Engl. J. Med.
source_full_journal_title: The New England journal of medicine

name: EID114
description_var_evidence: DNMT3A mutations (64.5% R882) were associated with older age, higher white blood cell count and cytogenetically normal AML in a large cohort of younger (18-60) AML patients.
source_name: Clinical impact of DNMT3A mutations in younger adult patients with acute myeloid leukemia: results of the AML Study Group (AMLSG).

name: EID115
description_var_evidence: DNMT3A R882 mutations were associated with cytogenetically normal AML in a large cohort of younger (18-60) AML patients.
source_name: Clinical impact of DNMT3A mutations in younger adult patients with acute myeloid leukemia: results of the AML Study Group (AMLSG).

name: EID116
description_var_evidence: AML with mutated NPM1 is a provisional entity in the World Health Organization (WHO) classification of acute myeloid leukemia (AML). This mutation should be tested for in clinical trials and is recommended for testing in patients with cytogentically normal AML.
source_name: The 2008 revision of the World Health Organization (WHO) classification of myeloid neoplasms and acute leukemia: rationale and important changes.

name: EID117
description_var_evidence: NPM1 mutations were associated with de novo AML as well as M4 and M5 FAB subtypes.
source_name: The impact of FLT3 internal tandem duplication mutant level, number, size, and interaction with NPM1 mutations in a large cohort of young adult patients with acute myeloid leukemia.

name: EID118
description_var_evidence: NPM1 mutations were associated with M4, M5a and M5b FAB subtypes of acute myeloid leukemia.
source_name: Nucleophosmin gene mutations are predictors of favorable prognosis in acute myelogenous leukemia with a normal karyotype.

name: EID119
description_var_evidence: NPM1 mutations were associated with M5a and M5b FAB subtypes of acute myeloid leukemia.
source_name: Prevalence and prognostic impact of NPM1 mutations in 1485 adult patients with acute myeloid leukemia (AML).

name: EID120
description_var_evidence: NPM1 mutations were associated with normal karyotype in older (>60) patients.
source_name: Gene mutations and response to treatment with all-trans retinoic acid in elderly patients with acute myeloid leukemia. Results from the AMLSG Trial AML HD98B.

name: EID121
description_var_evidence: NPM1 mutations were associated with intermediate risk cytogenetics (including normal karyotype).
source_name: DNMT3A mutations in acute myeloid leukemia.
source_citation: Ley et al., 2010, N. Engl. J. Med.
source_full_journal_title: The New England journal of medicine

name: EID122
description_var_evidence: In a randomized trial of previously untreated younger (<60) patients with acute myeloid leukemia (excluding acute promyelocytic leukemia) and high-risk myelodysplastic syndrome CEBPA mutation status had no significant impact on patient response to ATRA (N=20) compared to randomized control (N=15).
source_name: The impact on outcome of the addition of all-trans retinoic acid to intensive chemotherapy in younger patients with nonacute promyelocytic acute myeloid leukemia: overall results and results in genotypic subgroups defined by mutations in NPM1, FLT3, and CEBPA.

name: EID123
description_var_evidence: In chemotherapy-refractory patients with colorectal cancer, Exon 9 PIK3CA mutations (Exon 9) had no significant impact on response rate, disease control rate, progression free surivival or overall survival following cetuximab plus chemotherapy than those with wildtype PIK3CA.
source_name: Effects of KRAS, BRAF, NRAS, and PIK3CA mutations on the efficacy of cetuximab plus chemotherapy in chemotherapy-refractory metastatic colorectal cancer: a retrospective consortium analysis.
source_citation: De Roock et al., 2010, Lancet Oncol.

name: EID124
description_var_evidence: In chemotherapy-refractory patients with colorectal cancer, NRAS mutation status (primarily Q61) was not informative for disease control rate, progression free survival or overall survival following cetuximab plus chemotherapy.
source_name: Effects of KRAS, BRAF, NRAS, and PIK3CA mutations on the efficacy of cetuximab plus chemotherapy in chemotherapy-refractory metastatic colorectal cancer: a retrospective consortium analysis.
source_citation: De Roock et al., 2010, Lancet Oncol.

name: EID125
description_var_evidence: Cells lines expressing ALK harboring the F1174L mutation are less sensitive to growth inhibition by crizotinib than cells expressing the R1275Q mutation.
source_name: Differential inhibitor sensitivity of anaplastic lymphoma kinase variants found in neuroblastoma.
source_citation: Bresler et al., 2011, Sci Transl Med

name: EID126
description_var_evidence: Chemotherapy-refractory patients with colorectal cancer harboring BRAF mutations had lower response and disease control rates as well as shorter progression free and overall survival following cetuximab plus chemotherapy than those with wildtype BRAF.
source_name: Effects of KRAS, BRAF, NRAS, and PIK3CA mutations on the efficacy of cetuximab plus chemotherapy in chemotherapy-refractory metastatic colorectal cancer: a retrospective consortium analysis.
source_citation: De Roock et al., 2010, Lancet Oncol.

name: EID127
description_var_evidence: ATRA treatment did not effect overall survival in patients <60 years old with FLT3-ITD mutation.
source_name: The impact on outcome of the addition of all-trans retinoic acid to intensive chemotherapy in younger patients with nonacute promyelocytic acute myeloid leukemia: overall results and results in genotypic subgroups defined by mutations in NPM1, FLT3, and CEBPA.

name: EID128
description_var_evidence: FLT3-ITD mutation without NPM1 was associated with increased relapse risk and reduced overall survival in young adult AML patients (median age 43).
source_name: The impact of FLT3 internal tandem duplication mutant level, number, size, and interaction with NPM1 mutations in a large cohort of young adult patients with acute myeloid leukemia.

name: EID129
description_var_evidence: Increasing level of FLT3-ITD mutant correlated with reduced disease-free and overall survival as well as increased relapse rate.
source_name: The impact of FLT3 internal tandem duplication mutant level, number, size, and interaction with NPM1 mutations in a large cohort of young adult patients with acute myeloid leukemia.

name: EID130
description_var_evidence: Ba/F3 cells with both FLT3-ITD and TKD mutations on the same allele have more resistance to daunorubicin than cells with FLT3-ITD alone.
source_name: FLT3-ITD-TKD dual mutants associated with AML confer resistance to FLT3 PTK inhibitors and cytotoxic agents by overexpression of Bcl-x(L).

name: EID131
description_var_evidence: Ba/F3 cells with both FLT3-ITD and TKD mutations on the same allele have more resistance to the protein tyrosine kinase (PTK) inhibitor SU5614 than cells with FLT3-ITD alone or FLT3 ITD and TKD mutations on opposing alleles.
source_name: FLT3-ITD-TKD dual mutants associated with AML confer resistance to FLT3 PTK inhibitors and cytotoxic agents by overexpression of Bcl-x(L).

name: EID134
description_var_evidence: Chemotherapy-refractory patients with colorectal cancer harboring KRAS mutations (primarily G12/G13) had lower response and disease control rates and shorter progression free and overall survival following cetuximab plus chemotherapy than those with wildtype KRAS.
source_name: Effects of KRAS, BRAF, NRAS, and PIK3CA mutations on the efficacy of cetuximab plus chemotherapy in chemotherapy-refractory metastatic colorectal cancer: a retrospective consortium analysis.
source_citation: De Roock et al., 2010, Lancet Oncol.

name: EID135
description_var_evidence: KRAS mutations were significantly associated with lack of response to cetuximab in patients with advanced colorectal cancer.
source_name: KRAS mutations as an independent prognostic factor in patients with advanced colorectal cancer treated with cetuximab.
source_citation: LiÃ¨vre et al., 2008, J. Clin. Oncol.
source_full_journal_title: Journal of clinical oncology : official journal of the American Society of Clinical Oncology

name: EID136
description_var_evidence: Cells harboring KRAS G12V mutation were insensitive to cetuximab treatment in isogenic SW48 cells and in a mouse xenograft model.
source_name: Association of KRAS p.G13D mutation with outcome in patients with chemotherapy-refractory metastatic colorectal cancer treated with cetuximab.

name: EID137
description_var_evidence: ATRA treatment did not effect overall survival in patients <60 years old with NPM1 mutation regardless of FLT3-ITD status.
source_name: The impact on outcome of the addition of all-trans retinoic acid to intensive chemotherapy in younger patients with nonacute promyelocytic acute myeloid leukemia: overall results and results in genotypic subgroups defined by mutations in NPM1, FLT3, and CEBPA.

name: EID138
description_var_evidence: Chemotherapy-refractory patients with colorectal cancer harboring Exon 20 PIK3CA mutations had lower response and disease control rates as well as shorter progression free and overall survival following cetuximab plus chemotherapy than those with wildtype PIK3CA.
source_name: Effects of KRAS, BRAF, NRAS, and PIK3CA mutations on the efficacy of cetuximab plus chemotherapy in chemotherapy-refractory metastatic colorectal cancer: a retrospective consortium analysis.
source_citation: De Roock et al., 2010, Lancet Oncol.

name: EID139
description_var_evidence: WT1 mutations were associated with an inferior response to induction chemotherapy with a higher rate of resistant disease in young (15-60+, median 45) patients with cytogenetically normal AML.
source_name: Mutation of the Wilms' tumor 1 gene is a poor prognostic factor associated with chemotherapy resistance in normal karyotype acute myeloid leukemia: the United Kingdom Medical Research Council Adult Leukaemia Working Party.
source_citation: Virappane et al., 2008, J. Clin. Oncol.
source_full_journal_title: Journal of clinical oncology : official journal of the American Society of Clinical Oncology

name: EID141
description_var_evidence: CH5424802 treatment resulted in significant tumor regression in xenograft models produced from Ba/F3 cells expressing EML4-ALK or EML4-ALK with the L1196M mutation.
source_name: CH5424802, a selective ALK inhibitor capable of blocking the resistant gatekeeper mutant.

name: EID142
description_var_evidence: SH-SY5Y and Kelly cells with mutant ALK (F1174L) and Ba/F3 cells overexpressing ALK harboring the F1174L mutation are sensitive to TAE684-mediated growth inhibition.
source_name: Activating mutations in ALK provide a therapeutic target in neuroblastoma.

name: EID143
description_var_evidence: Cells lines expressing ALK harboring the F1174L mutation are less sensitive to growth inhibition by crizotinib than cells expressing the R1275Q mutation.
source_name: Differential inhibitor sensitivity of anaplastic lymphoma kinase variants found in neuroblastoma.
source_citation: Bresler et al., 2011, Sci Transl Med

name: EID144
description_var_evidence: Following identification of this fusion in a patient, this fusion was expressed in HEK 293T cells leading to oligomerization in the absence of ligand, induced morphologic changes in the cell and increased cellular proliferation consistent with FGFR activation. Mouse xenografts using the bladder cell line SW780 which harbors an FGFR3-BAIAP2L1 fusion showed reduced tumor burden when treated with the FGFR inhibitor PD173074.
source_name: Identification of targetable FGFR gene fusions in diverse cancers.

name: EID145
description_var_evidence: Cells harboring KRAS G13D mutation were sensitive to cetuximab treatment in isogenic SW48 cells and in a mouse xenograft model.
source_name: Association of KRAS p.G13D mutation with outcome in patients with chemotherapy-refractory metastatic colorectal cancer treated with cetuximab.

name: EID146
description_var_evidence: ATRA treatment improved overall and relapse-free survival in older (>60) patients with mutant NPM1 and without FLT3-ITD.
source_name: Gene mutations and response to treatment with all-trans retinoic acid in elderly patients with acute myeloid leukemia. Results from the AMLSG Trial AML HD98B.

name: EID147
description_var_evidence: Young patients (18-60) with NPM1 mutations had improved overall survival following high-dose versus standard dose daunorubicin (p=0.01) in univariate analysis. However, the adjusted p-value for multiple testing is 0.11.
source_name: Prognostic relevance of integrated genetic profiling in acute myeloid leukemia.
source_citation: Patel et al., 2012, N. Engl. J. Med.
source_full_journal_title: The New England journal of medicine

name: EID148
description_var_evidence: For patients with NPM1 mutation that achieved CR following induction therapy, relapse-free survival was improved following treatment with valproic acid.
source_name: Valproic acid in combination with all-trans retinoic acid and intensive therapy for acute myeloid leukemia in older patients.

name: EID149
description_var_evidence: NSC348884 combined with ATRA treatment induces apoptosis in primary AML cells harboring mutant NPM1 but not in cells with wildtype NPM1 or both mutant NPM1 and FLT3-ITD.
source_name: Targeting levels or oligomerization of nucleophosmin 1 induces differentiation and loss of survival of human AML cells with mutant NPM1.

name: EID150
description_var_evidence: CD33 and CD123 expression was significantly increased in patients with NPM1 mutation with FLT3-ITD, indicating these patients may respond to combined anti-CD33 and anti-CD123 therapy.
source_name: Distribution and levels of cell surface expression of CD33 and CD123 in acute myeloid leukemia.
source_citation: Ehninger et al., 2014, Blood Cancer J

name: EID151
description_var_evidence: CD33 expression was significantly increased in patients with NPM1 mutation with or without FLT3-ITD, indicating these patients may respond to anti-CD33 therapy.
source_name: Distribution and levels of cell surface expression of CD33 and CD123 in acute myeloid leukemia.
source_citation: Ehninger et al., 2014, Blood Cancer J

name: EID152
description_var_evidence: NSC348884 induced apoptosis in OPI-AML3 cells harboring an NPM1 mutation.
source_name: Targeting levels or oligomerization of nucleophosmin 1 induces differentiation and loss of survival of human AML cells with mutant NPM1.

name: EID153
description_var_evidence: NPM1 mutation (Type A, W288fs) causes cytoplasmic localization of NPM when transfected into a non-hematopoietic cell line (293T cells). Cytoplasmic localization of NPM in AML patients was associated with good response to induction therapy.
source_name: Cytoplasmic nucleophosmin in acute myelogenous leukemia with a normal karyotype.
source_citation: Falini et al., 2005, N. Engl. J. Med.
source_full_journal_title: The New England journal of medicine

name: EID154
description_var_evidence: Following rapamycin treatment of mice with KrasG12D-induced lung tumors, mice with Tsc1 deletion (exon17/18 deletion resulting in frameshift) in the lung exhibit increased overall survival, increased apoptosis, reduced proliferation and reduced tumor burden compared to Tsc1 wildtype mice.
source_name: TSC1 loss synergizes with KRAS activation in lung cancer development in the mouse and confers rapamycin sensitivity.

name: EID155
description_var_evidence: Tumors expressing TSC1 or TSC2 mutations show notably more sensitivity to everolimus than their wild-type counterparts.
source_name: Genome sequencing identifies a basis for everolimus sensitivity.

name: EID156
description_var_evidence: FLT3 mutations did not alter overall survival or remission duration in younger (16-60), cytogenetically normal AML patients with CEBPA mutations. 10/36 patients with CEBPA mutations also had FLT3 mutations (8 FLT3-ITD, 2 FLT3-D835).
source_name: CEBPA mutations in younger adults with acute myeloid leukemia and normal cytogenetics: prognostic relevance and analysis of cooperating mutations.
source_citation: FrÃ¶hling et al., 2004, J. Clin. Oncol.
source_full_journal_title: Journal of clinical oncology : official journal of the American Society of Clinical Oncology

name: EID157
description_var_evidence: Complete remission rates did not differ between patients with wildtype or mutant DNMT3A (62% of which affected R882) and cytogenetically normal AML.
source_name: Age-related prognostic impact of different types of DNMT3A mutations in adults with primary cytogenetically normal acute myeloid leukemia.
source_citation: Marcucci et al., 2012, J. Clin. Oncol.
source_full_journal_title: Journal of clinical oncology : official journal of the American Society of Clinical Oncology

name: EID158
description_var_evidence: FLT3-ITD duplication length did not effect prognosis in patients with an NPM1 mutation.
source_name: Prognostic impact of FLT3-ITD load in NPM1 mutated acute myeloid leukemia.

name: EID159
description_var_evidence: Size of the FLT3-ITD mutant duplication had no impact on overall survival or relapse rate.
source_name: The impact of FLT3 internal tandem duplication mutant level, number, size, and interaction with NPM1 mutations in a large cohort of young adult patients with acute myeloid leukemia.

name: EID160
description_var_evidence: Mutation status of IDH1 did not change event-free survival of patients with an NPM1 mutation.
source_name: IDH1 mutations are detected in 6.6% of 1414 AML patients and are associated with intermediate risk karyotype and unfavorable prognosis in adults younger than 60 years and unmutated NPM1 status.

name: EID162
description_var_evidence: No differences in relapse-free or overall survival were identified between young (16-60) patients with or without WT1 mutations (69% exon 7, 15% exon 9) in cytogenetically normal AML.
source_name: Prognostic impact of WT1 mutations in cytogenetically normal acute myeloid leukemia: a study of the German-Austrian AML Study Group.

name: EID163
description_var_evidence: Rates of complete remission and refractory disease are not different in patients with WT1 mutations (69% exon 7, 15% exon 9) than those without in young (16-60) patients with cytogenetically normal AML.
source_name: Prognostic impact of WT1 mutations in cytogenetically normal acute myeloid leukemia: a study of the German-Austrian AML Study Group.

name: EID165
description_var_evidence: Rates of complete remission and refractory disease are not different in patients with WT1 mutations (69% exon 7, 15% exon 9) than those without in young (16-60) patients with cytogenetically normal AML.
source_name: Prognostic impact of WT1 mutations in cytogenetically normal acute myeloid leukemia: a study of the German-Austrian AML Study Group.

name: EID166
description_var_evidence: In a group of young (<60 years old) acute myeloid leukemia (exclude acute promyelocytic leukemia) and high-risk MDS patients, those with CEBPA mutations (35/423) showed marginally improved overall survival (36% vs 31%; P = .04) than those with wildtype CEBPA.
source_name: The impact on outcome of the addition of all-trans retinoic acid to intensive chemotherapy in younger patients with nonacute promyelocytic acute myeloid leukemia: overall results and results in genotypic subgroups defined by mutations in NPM1, FLT3, and CEBPA.

name: EID167
description_var_evidence: In young patients (age 16-60) with previously untreated, cytogenetically normal acute myeloid leukemia, CEBPA mutation was significantly associated with complete remission in multivariate analysis (odds ratio, 1.33; 95% confidence interval [CI], 1.01 to 1.74). Multivariate analysis was performed on all patients  that were evaluated for a mutation in at least 1 gene (CEBPA, FLT3-ITD or NPM1) totaling 693/872 patients in the study. Only 509 patients in the study were evaluated for CEBPA, 67 of which had a mutation.
source_name: Mutations and treatment outcome in cytogenetically normal acute myeloid leukemia.
source_citation: Schlenk et al., 2008, N. Engl. J. Med.
source_full_journal_title: The New England journal of medicine

name: EID168
description_var_evidence: Overall survival and remission duration were significantly longer (p=0.01 and p=0.05, respectively) in younger (16-60), cytogenetically normal acute myeloid leukemia patients with CEBPA mutations (21/236 patients).
source_name: CEBPA mutations in younger adults with acute myeloid leukemia and normal cytogenetics: prognostic relevance and analysis of cooperating mutations.
source_citation: FrÃ¶hling et al., 2004, J. Clin. Oncol.
source_full_journal_title: Journal of clinical oncology : official journal of the American Society of Clinical Oncology

name: EID170
description_var_evidence: DNMT3A mutations were associated with achievement of complete remission in a large cohort of younger (18-60) AML patients.
source_name: Clinical impact of DNMT3A mutations in younger adult patients with acute myeloid leukemia: results of the AML Study Group (AMLSG).

name: EID171
description_var_evidence: Event-free survival was significantly improved in patients with both NPM1 and FLT3-TKD mutations compared to patients with 1) FLT3-TKD mutations alone 2) either NPM1 or FLT3-TKD when FLT3-ITD patients were excluded from the analysis 3) neither FLT3-TKD or NPM1 mutations or FLT3-TKD alone when only de novo, normal karyotype patients were analyzed.
source_name: Prognostic relevance of FLT3-TKD mutations in AML: the combination matters--an analysis of 3082 patients.

name: EID172
description_var_evidence: MGMT promoter methylation was associated with increased overall and disease-free survival as well as tumor regression in patients with gliomas.
source_name: Inactivation of the DNA-repair gene MGMT and the clinical response of gliomas to alkylating agents.
source_citation: Esteller et al., 2000, N. Engl. J. Med.
source_full_journal_title: The New England journal of medicine

name: EID173
description_var_evidence: NPM1 mutation without FLT3-ITD was associated with reduced relapse risk and increased overall survival in young adult acute myeloid leukemia patients (median age 43).
source_name: The impact of FLT3 internal tandem duplication mutant level, number, size, and interaction with NPM1 mutations in a large cohort of young adult patients with acute myeloid leukemia.

name: EID174
description_var_evidence: Patients with NPM1 mutations were associated with improved complete remission rates as well as overall and disease free survival when all ages and karyotype were analyzed; however, when only normal karyotype patients were analyzed, only complete remission rates were improved.
source_name: Gene mutations and response to treatment with all-trans retinoic acid in elderly patients with acute myeloid leukemia. Results from the AMLSG Trial AML HD98B.

name: EID175
description_var_evidence: Complete remission rates were higher (P<0.001) and both disease-free survival (N=205 vs 352, P=0.041) and overall survival (N=372 vs 956, P=0.022) were longer for AML patients with Exon 12 NPM1 mutations (irrespective of FLT3 status) than those with wildtype NPM1. Improved CR rates were also higher for those with NPM1 exon 12 mutations and normal karyotype. In multivariate analysis, NPM1 mutation alone (FLT3 wildtype) was associated with improved overall survival (but not DFS) in the entire cohort and in normal karyotype patients <60 years old.
source_name: Prevalence and prognostic impact of NPM1 mutations in 1485 adult patients with acute myeloid leukemia (AML).

name: EID176
description_var_evidence: Complete remission rates were higher (70.5% vs 54.7%, P = 0.003) and event-free survival was longer (median, 428 vs 336 days; P = 0.012) for normal karyotype AML patients (median age 60.3 years) with Exon 12 NPM1 mutations (N=212) compared to those with wildtype NPM1 (N=189).
source_name: Nucleophosmin gene mutations are predictors of favorable prognosis in acute myelogenous leukemia with a normal karyotype.

name: EID177
description_var_evidence: Cytoplasmic localization of NPM in AML patients was an independent prognositic factor associated with complete remission in response to induction therapy in a multivariate analysis (p=0.019) but not in a univariate analysis (p=0.07).
source_name: Cytoplasmic nucleophosmin in acute myelogenous leukemia with a normal karyotype.
source_citation: Falini et al., 2005, N. Engl. J. Med.
source_full_journal_title: The New England journal of medicine

name: EID179
description_var_evidence: Intermediate risk patients with mutant NPM1 had improved overall survival with the presence of either IDH1 or IDH2 mutations than those wildtype for both IDH1 and IDH2.
source_name: Prognostic relevance of integrated genetic profiling in acute myeloid leukemia.
source_citation: Patel et al., 2012, N. Engl. J. Med.
source_full_journal_title: The New England journal of medicine

name: EID180
description_var_evidence: Normal karyotype patients with NPM1 mutation and without FLT3-ITD had improved overall and relapse-free survival, complete remission rates and remission duration compared to all other combinations of mutants.
source_name: Age-related risk profile and chemotherapy dose response in acute myeloid leukemia: a study by the German Acute Myeloid Leukemia Cooperative Group.
source_citation: BÃ¼chner et al., 2009, J. Clin. Oncol.
source_full_journal_title: Journal of clinical oncology : official journal of the American Society of Clinical Oncology

name: EID181
description_var_evidence: NPM1 mutation (N=724) was associated with higher complete remission rates (92% vs 82%; P < 0.0001), lower cumulative incidence of relapse (42% vs 58%; P < 0.0001) and higher overall survival (48% vs 27%; P < .0001) than NPM1 wildtype status (N=885) in intermediate risk, young adult AML patients (median age 46 years).
source_name: Impact of FLT3(ITD) mutant allele level on relapse risk in intermediate-risk acute myeloid leukemia.

name: EID182
description_var_evidence: NPM1 mutation was associated with increased overall, event-free and relapse-free survival and remission after induction therapy in the entire cohort and in the cytogenetically normal subset of patients.
source_name: TET2 mutations in acute myeloid leukemia (AML): results from a comprehensive genetic and clinical analysis of the AML study group.
source_citation: Gaidzik et al., 2012, J. Clin. Oncol.
source_full_journal_title: Journal of clinical oncology : official journal of the American Society of Clinical Oncology

name: EID183
description_var_evidence: In young patients (age 16-60) with previously untreated, cytogenetically normal acute myeloid leukemia, NPM1 mutation without FLT3-ITD was significantly associated with complete remission in multivariate analysis (odds ratio, 1.48; 95% CI, 1.21 to 1.80). Multivariate analysis was performed on all patients that were evaluated for a mutation in at least 1 gene (CEBPA, FLT3-ITD or NPM1) totaling 693/872 patients in the study. 130 patients had NPM1 mutations without FLT3-ITD. NPM1 mutations were evaluated in 570 patients (310 mutated).  FLT3-ITD was evaluated in 531 patients (164 mutated).
source_name: Mutations and treatment outcome in cytogenetically normal acute myeloid leukemia.
source_citation: Schlenk et al., 2008, N. Engl. J. Med.
source_full_journal_title: The New England journal of medicine

name: EID184
description_var_evidence: NPM1 mutations were associated with increased complete remission rates as well as longer overall disease free survival in normal karyotype AML patients >59 years old, particularly in those >69 years old.
source_name: Favorable prognostic impact of NPM1 mutations in older patients with cytogenetically normal de novo acute myeloid leukemia and associated gene- and microRNA-expression signatures: a Cancer and Leukemia Group B study.
source_citation: Becker et al., 2010, J. Clin. Oncol.
source_full_journal_title: Journal of clinical oncology : official journal of the American Society of Clinical Oncology

name: EID185
description_var_evidence: Younger (16-60), normal karyotype AML patients with Exon 12 NPM1 mutation and without FLT3-ITD have increased overall survival (N=74, P = .001), relapse-free survival (N=86, P < .001) and response to induction chemotherapy. Multivariate analysis identified NPM1 mutation in the absence of FLT3-ITD as a prognostic marker for the achievement of CR (P=0.004).
source_name: Mutant nucleophosmin (NPM1) predicts favorable prognosis in younger adults with acute myeloid leukemia and normal cytogenetics: interaction with other gene mutations.

name: EID186
description_var_evidence: Complete remission rate was not different between young AML patients (<60 years old) with or without DNMT3A mutations (60% of which were R882).
source_name: Mutant DNMT3A: a marker of poor prognosis in acute myeloid leukemia.

name: EID187
description_var_evidence: DNMT3A mutations (62% of which were R882) were associated with reduced disease-free survival in patients with cytogenetically normal AML.
source_name: Age-related prognostic impact of different types of DNMT3A mutations in adults with primary cytogenetically normal acute myeloid leukemia.
source_citation: Marcucci et al., 2012, J. Clin. Oncol.
source_full_journal_title: Journal of clinical oncology : official journal of the American Society of Clinical Oncology

name: EID188
description_var_evidence: Young AML patients (415 patients; <60 years old) with any DNMT3A mutation (n=96) have shorter overall survival and relapse-free survival than patients with wildtype DNMT3A.
source_name: Mutant DNMT3A: a marker of poor prognosis in acute myeloid leukemia.

name: EID189
description_var_evidence: Young AML patients (415 patients; <60 years old) with DNMT3A R882 mutations (n=58) have shorter overall and relapse-free survival than patients with wildtype DNMT3A.
source_name: Mutant DNMT3A: a marker of poor prognosis in acute myeloid leukemia.

name: EID190
description_var_evidence: Meta-analysis of studies involving cytogentically normal younger (<60) patients showed reduced overall and relapse-free survival for patients with FLT3-ITD.
source_name: Prognostic significance of FLT3 internal tandem duplication, nucleophosmin 1, and CEBPA gene mutations for acute myeloid leukemia patients with normal karyotype and younger than 60 years: a systematic review and meta-analysis.

name: EID191
description_var_evidence: A ratio of >0.49 FLT3-ITD/FLT3 wildtype level was associated with reduced event-free and overall survival in old (>59) and younger patients (<60) with an NPM1 mutation.
source_name: Prognostic impact of FLT3-ITD load in NPM1 mutated acute myeloid leukemia.

name: EID192
description_var_evidence: Patients with NPM1 mutation and FLT3-ITD had reduced event-free survival compared to patients with wildtype FLT3.
source_name: Prognostic impact of FLT3-ITD load in NPM1 mutated acute myeloid leukemia.

name: EID193
description_var_evidence: Using a ratio of FLT3-ITD/FLT3 wildtype levels as a continuous variable, a higher ratio was associated with reduced event-free survival in patients with an NPM1 mutation.
source_name: Prognostic impact of FLT3-ITD load in NPM1 mutated acute myeloid leukemia.

name: EID194
description_var_evidence: KRAS mutations were significantly associated with reduced progression-free and overall survival in patients with advanced colorectal cancer.
source_name: KRAS mutations as an independent prognostic factor in patients with advanced colorectal cancer treated with cetuximab.
source_citation: LiÃ¨vre et al., 2008, J. Clin. Oncol.
source_full_journal_title: Journal of clinical oncology : official journal of the American Society of Clinical Oncology

name: EID195
description_var_evidence: Coocurrence of FLT3-ITD mutations significantly reduced overall (N=74 vs 95, P=0.003) and disease-free survival (N=43 vs 67, P=0.02) of normal karyotype AML patients (<60 years old) compared to patients with NPM1 mutations alone.
source_name: Prevalence and prognostic impact of NPM1 mutations in 1485 adult patients with acute myeloid leukemia (AML).

name: EID196
description_var_evidence: Monitoring NPM1 mutation by cDNA-based RT-PCR effectively predicted relapse in 62/93 patients by >1 log increase in NPM1 levels (N=57) or lack of reduction in NPM1 levels following first line therapy (N=15).
source_name: Minimal residual disease levels assessed by NPM1 mutation-specific RQ-PCR provide important prognostic information in AML.

name: EID198
description_var_evidence: Patients with NPM1 mutations and low (<25%, N=63), intermediate (25-50%, N=156) or high (>50%, N=66) levels of FLT3-ITD have worse overall survival (P<0.0001 for trend) and cumulative incidence of relapse (P<0.001) than those with NPM1 mutations alone (N=387) in young adult, intermediate risk AML patients.
source_name: Impact of FLT3(ITD) mutant allele level on relapse risk in intermediate-risk acute myeloid leukemia.

name: EID199
description_var_evidence: TET2 mutation reduces overall survival of normal karyotype patients with either an NPM1 mutation or NPM1 mutation without FLT3-ITD.
source_name: TET2 gene mutation is unfavorable prognostic factor in cytogenetically normal acute myeloid leukemia patients with NPM1+ and FLT3-ITD - mutations.
source_citation: Tian et al., 2014, Int. J. Hematol.

name: EID201
description_var_evidence: Mutations  in WT1 were associated with increased risk of recurrence in young patients (15-50) with cytogenetically normal AML.
source_name: Wilms tumor 1 gene mutations are associated with a higher risk of recurrence in young adults with acute myeloid leukemia: a study from the Acute Leukemia French Association.

name: EID202
description_var_evidence: Mutations in WT1 were associated with a worse overall prognosis than patients wildtype for WT1 in young patients (15-50), primarily because of increased risk of disease recurrence.
source_name: Wilms tumor 1 gene mutations are associated with a higher risk of recurrence in young adults with acute myeloid leukemia: a study from the Acute Leukemia French Association.

name: EID203

name: EID205

name: EID206
description_var_evidence: WT1 mutations were associated with a higher cumulative incidence of relapse and shorter relapse free survival in young (15-60+, median 45) patients with cytogenetically normal AML.
source_name: Mutation of the Wilms' tumor 1 gene is a poor prognostic factor associated with chemotherapy resistance in normal karyotype acute myeloid leukemia: the United Kingdom Medical Research Council Adult Leukaemia Working Party.
source_citation: Virappane et al., 2008, J. Clin. Oncol.
source_full_journal_title: Journal of clinical oncology : official journal of the American Society of Clinical Oncology

description_var_evidence: WT1 mutations were associated with shorter overall and disease free survival in a cohort of cytogenetically normal, young (<60) AML patients.

name: EID211
description_var_evidence: The combination of PARP inhibition (Olaparib) with BRCA mutation results in irreparable and lethal DNA damage. Response rates are higher in BRCA1 mutation positive women with high grade serous or undifferentiated ovarian cancer.

name: EID212

name: EID236
description_var_evidence: A 28 year old patient with T4N3M1 stage lung adenocarcinoma harboring an EML4-ALK variant 1 fusion was treated with crizotinib after failing conventional therapy. The patient achieved a partial response but progressed after 5 months of treatment. Molecular analysis at this time identified two missense mutations in ALK C1156Y and L1196M. Ba/F3 cells expressing EML4-ALK L1196M or EML4-ALK C1156Y were more resistant to crizontinib treatment than those expressing EML4-ALK wildtype.

description_var_evidence: In a single patient with this fusion in intrahepatic cholangiocarcinoma. Ponatinib treatment resulted in necrosis and shrinkage of the primary and metastatic sites and overall stable disease. However, this response did not meet criteria for RECIST partial response.
source_name: Integrated genomic characterization reveals novel, therapeutically relevant drug targets in FGFR and EGFR pathways in sporadic intrahepatic cholangiocarcinoma.

name: EID296
description_var_evidence: In a 43 year old female patient with this fusion in intrahepatic cholangiocarcinoma. Both pazopanib and ponatinib separately resulted in minor tumor shrinkage. This fusion is also shown to be recurrent in multiple other cancer types.
source_name: Integrated genomic characterization reveals novel, therapeutically relevant drug targets in FGFR and EGFR pathways in sporadic intrahepatic cholangiocarcinoma.

name: EID297
description_var_evidence: CEP701 was effective in reducing blast counts of 5/14 heavily pre-treated AML patients with FLT3 mutations.
source_name: Single-agent CEP-701, a novel FLT3 inhibitor, shows biologic and clinical activity in patients with relapsed or refractory acute myeloid leukemia.

name: EID298
description_var_evidence: Sorafenib is effective in patients with FLT3 internal tandem repeats, but not in wild type or D835 mutation.

name: EID299
description_var_evidence: AG1296 is effective in triggering apoptosis in Ba/F3 and primary AML cells with FLT3 internal tandem repeat.
source_name: Inhibition of the transforming activity of FLT3 internal tandem duplication mutants from AML patients by a tyrosine kinase inhibitor.

name: EID301
description_var_evidence: Targeting overactive GATA2-mediated pathways with inhibitors bortezomib and fasudil led to dramatic tumor regression.
source_name: The GATA2 transcriptional network is requisite for RAS oncogene-driven non-small cell lung cancer.

name: EID302
description_var_evidence: In a case study, a patient with anal melanoma harboring a 7 codon duplication in the juxtamambrane region (exon 11) of KIT showed marked response 4 months after imatinib treatment.
source_name: Major response to imatinib mesylate in KIT-mutated melanoma.
source_citation: Hodi et al., 2008, J. Clin. Oncol.

name: EID303

source_name: L576P KIT mutation in anal melanomas correlates with KIT protein expression and is sensitive to specific kinase inhibition.

name: EID304

source_name: Efficacy of the kinase inhibitor SU11248 against gastrointestinal stromal tumor mutants refractory to imatinib mesylate.
source_citation: Prenen et al., 2006, Clin. Cancer Res.
source_full_journal_title: Clinical cancer research : an official journal of the American Association for Cancer Research

name: EID305
description_var_evidence: The use of NVP-BEZ235 in conjunction with ARRY-142886, but not as monotherapy, in a lung cancer model with KRAS G12D mutation led to marked tumor regression.
source_name: Effective use of PI3K and MEK inhibitors to treat mutant Kras G12D and PIK3CA H1047R murine lung cancers.

name: EID306

name: EID307

source_full_journal_title: The New England journal of medicine

name: EID308
description_var_evidence: MGMT promoter methylation has been shown to confer sensitivity to alkylating agents, such as carmustine, in glioblastoma cells.
source_name: Inactivation of the DNA-repair gene MGMT and the clinical response of gliomas to alkylating agents.

source_full_journal_title: The New England journal of medicine

name: EID309
description_var_evidence: In patients lacking MGMT promoter methylation, the use of an MGMT inhibitor, such as O(6)-benzylguanine, in combination with alkylating agents (Carmustine) may be useful in treating patients with initial resistance to alkylating agents.
source_name: Inactivation of the DNA-repair gene MGMT and the clinical response of gliomas to alkylating agents.

name: EID310

name: EID311

source_full_journal_title: Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America

name: EID314
description_var_evidence: Breast cancer cell lines with H1047R mutation showed increased sensitivity to CH5132799 than cells with wild-type PIK3CA gene.
source_name: The selective class I PI3K inhibitor CH5132799 targets human cancers harboring oncogenic PIK3CA mutations.
source_citation: Tanaka et al., 2011, Clin. Cancer Res.

description_var_evidence: Breast tumors in a mouse model with R175H mutation are more responsive to doxorubicin than breast tumors with wild type TP53.

name: EID320
description_var_evidence: A patient with metastatic bladder cancer that responded well to the mTOR inhibitor everolimus was shown to harbor a TSC1 frameshift truncation mutation (c.1907_1908del, p.Glu636fs) and a nonsense NF2 mutation. 2/3 additional patients with TSC1 mutations also had mild responses to everolimus.

name: EID322

name: EID324

name: EID328

name: EID329

name: EID330

name: EID331

name: EID332

name: EID333

name: EID336

name: EID337

description_var_evidence: After adjusting for age and cancer stage, the presence of U2AF mutations such as S34Y/F are prognostic for poorer survival outcomes in patients with MDS.
source_name: Clinical implications of U2AF1 mutation in patients with myelodysplastic syndrome and its stability during disease progression.

name: EID403
description_var_evidence: Cell lines with MEF2D-CSF1R fusion show sensitivity to the tyrosine kinase inhibitors Imatinib and GW-2580.

name: EID405
description_var_evidence: A head-to-tail in-frame fusion between exon1 of DNAJB1 and exon2 of PRKACA resulting from a ~400kb deletion was observed in 100% (15/15) fibrolamellar hepatocellular carcinomas examined. The fusion was confirmed at both RNA and DNA level in all primary and metastatic tumor samples but not in adjacent normal tissue. Immunoprecipitation and Western blot analyses confirmed that the chimeric protein is expressed in tumor tissue, and a cell culture assay indicated that it retains kinase activity.
source_name: Detection of a recurrent DNAJB1-PRKACA chimeric transcript in fibrolamellar hepatocellular carcinoma.

name: EID407
description_var_evidence: The t(14;18) transloaction of BCL2 is shown to be associated with germinal-center B-cellâ€“like diffuse large-B-cell lymphomas.

source_citation: Rosenwald et al., 2002, N. Engl. J. Med.
source_full_journal_title: The New England journal of medicine

name: EID408
description_var_evidence: Amplification of FOXP1 is shown to be associated with ABC DLBCL.
source_name: Molecular subtypes of diffuse large B-cell lymphoma arise by distinct genetic pathways.
source_citation: Lenz et al., 2008, Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U.S.A.
source_full_journal_title: Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America

name: EID409
description_var_evidence: Amplification of REL is shown to be associated with germinal-center B-cellâ€“like diffuse large-B-cell lymphomas.
source_name: The use of molecular profiling to predict survival after chemotherapy for diffuse large-B-cell lymphoma.
